  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7090.61 sitting just below the 7095 GEX flip in a PIN regime, dealers are currently buying the dip as spot trades below their hedge point, providing underlying support. The massive positive gamma wall at 7100 (+4995.3M) followed by even larger walls at 7150 and 7200 creates a strong magnet effect that should limit downside and pull price back toward these levels. Watch for increased dealer selling pressure if we break back above 7095-7100, with the 7200 strike acting as the primary resistance zone where dealers will aggressively sell rallies.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect a bounce back toward 7100-7150 with limited downside risk.",
